          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Note to self: for proper online anonymity, a good start is:<br /><br />1) have a good username/password manager, such as LastPass, KeePass, etc.<br />2) Use said manager for all website fora that aren't supposed to be at least partly for people you know in meatspace (i.e. not Facebook)<br />3) Each forum gets a unique username and randomly-generated password unrelated to any username used on any other site, stored in the manager<br />4) Create an email account on a free webmail service used only for forum registration, also with a username unrelated to anything you use for social-networking sites.<br /><br />Profit, or at least don't get doxed when you get famous.  I certainly wouldn't want some of the crap I said as a teen getting out if I got famous in my 50s, for instance.<br /><br />Annoying, though, because having a pseudonym consistent across websites means that you can serendipitously meet friends from other sites.

              

              
              
            </div>
