              There's quite a few issues with the last two articles by Joe, but my personal complaint is that they're just poorly written articles that sound like they were banged out in 30minutes. The second article in particular (the on Snowden) doesn't offer anything except a collection of quotes, with no direction, interpretation, or discussion. I feel the same way about <a href="http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2013/03/lets-hope-it-clears-the-chasm-openforum-talks-tomb-raider-reboot/" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">Cesar Torres' articles about forum posts</a>. In both cases, they basically boil down to &quot;Hey guys! This guy said this, and then this guy said this!  And then this girl said this!&quot;  <br /><br />Seriously, just use a bot to scrape the forum and write these articles and they'd come out the same.

              

              
              
