              <div class="quotetitle"><a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/viewtopic.php?p=24709909#p24709909" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">hux</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That's <span style="font-style: italic">very</span> different from Ars going into its private, secured registration database and then publicly announcing that, yes, [forum name] == [real name], oh and here's the email address he used to register at our site.</div><br /><br />We did not &quot;confirm&quot; it was him in the manner you just depicted. We said it looked like him, which everyone else had _already said_ for the same exact reasons. Snowden published his registration email address himself, and had done so on other sites. We believe strongly that those posts are his, but not because of a database registration. In fact, the very idea that a simple email address can magically &quot;confirm&quot; someone's identity doesn't even make sense. There is nothing in his profile, public or otherwise, that can prove that it was him. The belief that it is him is based on circumstantial information, no different from that used by everyone else.<br /><br />This is why you will not find a single media report confirming that the posts were made by him. I was contacted by over a dozen major media outlets, and I could NOT confirm that it was him. And I have full access to everything. And even if I could personally have discovered this somehow, I would not have confirmed or reported that information. <br /><br />Finally, Joe does not have access to that database, no do editors in general. The number of people with that access is very limited.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
  <table id="p24710027" class="post odd read" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
      
        <tr>
          <td rowspan="2" class="post-author">
            <div class="post-author-inner">
              

              <div class="post-author-name"><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=998&amp;sid=f5ab5ebc880e479447e99e7f846b0069">Ken Fisher</a></div>
                <div class="post-author-title">
                  "Editor-in-Chief"<br />
                  Caesar Imperator
                  
                  <br>et <a href="http://arstechnica.com/subscriptions/">Subscriptor</a>
                  
	 
                </div>
              
              <div class="post-author-tribus"></div>
              <div class="post-author-registered">Registered: Feb 17, 1999</div><div class="post-author-postcount">Posts: 19204</div>
            </div>
          </td>
          <td class="post-date-actions">
            <div class="post-date-actions-inner">
              <div class="post-actions">
                
              </div>
              <div class="post-date">
                <a href="./viewtopic.php?p=24710027&amp;sid=f5ab5ebc880e479447e99e7f846b0069#p24710027">Posted: Fri Jun 14, 2013 10:25 am</a>
