              Thank you. I do appreciate the explanation, regardless of my agreeing/disagreeing with your decisions behind it.<br /><br />I think &quot;framing&quot; is rather too light a term for it personally, but at that stage we are arguing semantics, which is neither constructive, nor productive. <br /><br />I'm at least comfortable that it's something you'll think about in future.

              

              
              
